// =============================================================================
// Samavāya BI — Presentation Service
// =============================================================================
// The presentation service is the canvas layer of the BI platform. A
// Dashboard arranges Widgets in a grid; each Widget binds to something
// that produces data — a saved Report, a raw VisualQuery, or a scalar
// Measure. Embedding, realtime streaming, and templates live here too.
//
// Power BI equivalent: Dashboards + pinned tiles + live pages.
// Looker equivalent:   Dashboards + tiles bound to Looks or Queries.
//
// Consolidation notes
// -------------------
// This service absorbs three legacy protos:
//   * business/insights/dashboard/proto/dashboard.proto        (canvas + widgets)
//   * business/insights/dashboard/proto/dashboard_embed.proto  (signed embeds)
//   * business/insights/insightviewer/proto/insightviewer_realtime.proto (streams)
//
// Key design moves:
//   * Widgets are not re-implementations of reports. They are THIN bindings
//     that delegate execution to core/bi/report or core/bi/query. The
//     widget owns presentation; the report / query owns computation.
//   * Templates unify savedsearch's "quickstart queries", dashboard's
//     "template library", and the seeded YAML dashboards from Sprint 7.
//     All three land in the same `DashboardTemplate` message.
//   * Streaming (realtime) and unary (refresh) are the SAME data shape —
//     StreamDashboardData emits the same rows StreamReportResults would.
//
// Design principles
// -----------------
//   * A Dashboard has a Layout (grid config) and a set of Widgets.
//     Widget position changes are bulk-patchable — dragging 5 widgets
//     must not require 5 RPCs.
//   * Embed tokens are short-lived by default with explicit TTL and
//     per-token scope. A token can bind to a dashboard OR a report, never
//     both (different views, different data exposure risks).
//   * Dashboard sharing is separate from widget-level ACLs. Widgets
//     inherit dashboard visibility but cannot narrow it; the query +
//     report layers enforce their own RLS independently.
//   * Realtime channels map 1-to-1 with widgets. When a widget's bound
//     data source supports push (events, change streams), the channel
//     publishes; otherwise the widget is polled by the client and the
//     channel is not used.
//
// Related docs
// ------------
//   * docs/BI_CONSOLIDATION_ROADMAP.md — Sprint 6 implementation
//   * docs/adr/0001-bi-platform-consolidation.md
//   * docs/adr/0002-bi-proto-contracts.md
// =============================================================================

